transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Hey, Charles, I would like to cancel my subscription.

Speaker 2: Okay. One second. Kristen Richard in Brentwood, California.

Speaker 1: Yes, sir.

Speaker 2: All right. It does look like you are a VIP member here.

Speaker 1: Do you just not need the pills every single month and need to pause for a while?

Speaker 2: No, I actually do not like the side effects, to be honest.

Speaker 1: Okay. Were you getting like bad headaches, upset stomach?

Speaker 2: I was – it was just – I don't know. It was like an overall feeling.

Speaker 1: Like I just – my mood changed, like everything.

Speaker 2: Like I just – I don't know. It seemed almost kind of pointless.

Speaker 1: I tried it like a handful of times, and it was like the same result every single time.

Speaker 2: Interesting. Okay.

Speaker 1: Yeah, I even attempted to split the pill to try to see if maybe the – maybe too much,

Speaker 2: and I still got the same effect.

Speaker 1: Gotcha. Okay. So we are with Pfizer,

Speaker 2: so it's always very disappointing when our product isn't taking a positive effect on anybody.

Speaker 1: We do have a AGV version that's made in our France factory,

Speaker 2: so I don't know if you're still willing to see if we can provide anything

Speaker 1: to give you that kick that you're looking for.

Speaker 2: But if you'd like, I can message my pharmacy

Speaker 1: and have them send you a sample of that version that I just mentioned completely for free.

Speaker 2: And if this one has a better effect for you,

Speaker 1: just call us back and let us know how we can accommodate with it.

Speaker 2: I don't mind trying it.

Speaker 1: I just don't want to pay another fee for something I'm definitely not going to like.

Speaker 2: Once I'm finished with this phone call, I'm going to throw away the other ones

Speaker 1: because I just don't want them laying around.

Speaker 2: Yeah.

Speaker 1: I'm going to destroy them.

Speaker 2: Yeah, that's fine.

Speaker 1: So I'll make sure that we don't try to charge you or send you anything for the next –

Speaker 2: I'll give you five months to try them and then call us back between now and then

Speaker 1: and then work on a refill schedule that fits the bill for you, okay?

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Okay, sounds good.

Speaker 2: So I'll message the pharmacy right now.

Speaker 1: The pill that you're looking for will have the number 100 pressed onto it like a stamp.

Speaker 2: That's how you're able to tell the difference.

Speaker 1: And if you ever need me again, my extension is 0040, okay?

Speaker 2: 0040?

Speaker 1: Yes, correct.

Speaker 2: Okay, so 0040?

Speaker 1: Exactly.

Speaker 2: Perfect, just like Bond.

Speaker 1: Exactly.

Speaker 2: Love it.

Speaker 1: All righty, brother.

Speaker 2: I hope you have a good rest of your day, okay?

Speaker 1: Thank you.

Speaker 2: I appreciate it.

Speaker 1: All right, take care.

Speaker 2: Bye.

Speaker 1: Bye.
